Step 1 : Add a User in a kali linux
Command :- adduser username
Step 2 : Network Setting In Kali Linux
IP Address
Command :- sudo ifconfig -a
Step 3 : IP address and Netmask Network Configuration
Command:- sudo ifconfig eth0 192.168.1.10 netmask 255.255.255.0
Step 4 : Configure Services In Kali Linux
Command :- service ssh start
Command :- ssh username@hostname
Step 5 : Basic Command To Run , Enable , Start and Stop Services
Command :- systemctl [command] [service_name]
Step 6: To stop and restart the service in Linux, use the command:
Command :- sudo systemctl restart SERVICE_NAME
Command :- sudo systemctl stop SERVICE_NAME
Step 7: To Enable Services At Boot
Command :- sudo systemctl enable SERVICE_NAME
Step 8 : To display the list of services which are running In Kali Linux
Command :- sudo systemctl -t=service --state=running
Step 9 : Use the Sudo settings
Command :- sudo apt install -y software_name
Any Command Which Are Used With Sudo Give A User A Super User Advantage.
